    <briefdescription>
<para>RTOS wrapper for message queue support. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>RTOS wrapper for counting semaphore support.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>The <ref refid="class_m_queue" kindref="compound">MQueue</ref> class implements a C++ wrapper template of the kernel message queue API provided by the Zephyr operating system. See details in Zephyr <ulink url="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/latest/kernel/services/data_passing/message_queues.html">message queue documentation</ulink> or in <ulink url="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/apidoc/latest/group__msgq__apis.html">API documentation</ulink>. The <ref refid="class_m_queue" kindref="compound">MQueue</ref> class provides methods to put objects of concretized type T in the queue and to get objects from the queue. Furthermore it provides a method to count the number of objects in the queue and to print statistics.</para>
</simplesect>
<hruler/>
</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>The sema class implements a C++ wrapper of the semaphore API provided by the Zephyr operating system. See details in Zephyr <linebreak/>
 <ulink url="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/latest/kernel/services/synchronization/semaphores.html">semaphore documentation</ulink> or in <ulink url="https://docs.zephyrproject.org/apidoc/latest/group__semaphore__apis.html">API documentation</ulink>. The sema class provides methods to wait for the availibility of the semaphore and a method to signal the availibility. <dot>
 digraph Semaphore {
   rankdir=LR;
   subgraph {
     node [shape=point,label=&quot;&quot;,height=.04, fixedsize=true] ENTRY1;
     node [shape=circle, fontname=Helvetica, fontsize=10, height=1, fixedsize=true, label=&quot;Available&quot;] A;
     node [shape=circle, fontname=Helvetica, fontsize=10, height=1, fixedsize=true, label=&quot;Unavailable&quot;] U;
     node [shape=point,label=&quot;&quot;,height=.04, fixedsize=true] ENTRY2;
     
     ENTRY1 -&gt; A [ label=&quot;Initial count &gt; 0&quot; ];
     A     -&gt; U [ label=&quot;Aquire (count = 0)&quot; ];
     A     -&gt; U [ style=invis ];
     U     -&gt; A [ label=&quot;Release (count = 1)&quot; ];
     A:sw  -&gt; A [ label=&quot;Release (count = count + 1)&quot;, dir=back ];
     A     -&gt; A [ label=&quot;Aquire (count = count - 1)&quot; ];
     ENTRY2 -&gt; U [ label=&quot;Initial count = 0&quot; ];
     {rank = same; ENTRY2; U;}
   } 
 }
</dot>
 </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
